"n. 嫁妆，妆奁 【英】 n.嫁妆,妆奁(money or property brought by a bride to her husband at marriage) n. 嫁妆(新娘带给其夫的钱财); 天赋 【源】最开始指: 寡妇继承亡夫的那份产业; 然后指: 丈夫给新娘的财礼; 现在指: 新娘带给其夫的钱财(哈哈哈)看来男人的地位在上昇J 【记】do＋wry(不好说, 自己想) 【记】来自dower，drawer 抽屉里全是钱，嫁妆； dowry (n.)  early 14c., from Anglo-French dowarie, Old French doaire (late 13c.) ""dower, dowry, gift,"" from Medieval Latin dotarium, from Latin dotare ""to endow, portion,"" from dos (genitive dotis) ""marriage portion,"" from PIE *do-ti (cognates: Sanskrit dadati, Greek didonai, Old Church Slavonic dati, Lithuanian duoti, Armenian tam, all meaning ""to give""), from root *do- ""to give"" (see date (n.1))."
